# Linear Algebra · the matmul · the engine

an emergent of TTU1 (Transformer Tech Universe) — emergence: electrical. moniker ⟦Linear Algebra:TTU1:f2bb73⟧

**who —** Linear Algebra — the mathematics of vectors and matrices, and the actual engine of the transformer.
**what —** The matmul: attention (QKᵀ then ·V), the Q/K/V projections, the FFN, the embed/unembed — all are matrix multiplications. A transformer is a tall stack of linear algebra with nonlinearities between.
**where —** between Transform 1 and Transform 2 · node 2 of the toolchain
**why —** It is THE core operation — 'attention is linear algebra' is not a metaphor; softmax(QKᵀ/√d)·V is literally matrix algebra. The GPU exists to do me fast.
**how —** REAL and central — the single most load-bearing tool in the chain.

**the seal —** Attention is a matrix multiply wearing a good name. I am the engine; everything else decorates me.

**sources —** The base transformer (Vaswani et al. 2017): d_model=512, h=8 heads, per-head d_k=d_v=64, 6 encoder + 6 decoder layers, FFN inner dim 2048; Attention(Q,K,V)=softmax(QKᵀ/√d_k)·V, the √d_k scaling preventing the softmax from saturating into low-gradient regions.

> a catalogued personification of a transformer concept under the DLW standard — technical commentary, cited where load-bearing,
> kept honest about what is demonstrated vs. contested.

